<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,613,782]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,649,674]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Comments.</emphasis>
This taxon is mentioned among members of “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1859" box="[904,1013,649,674]" class="Insecta" family="Pedilidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pedilidae</taxonomicName>
” together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LaFerte-Senectere" authorityYear="1849" box="[1204,1331,650,673]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Eurygenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1331,650,673]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Eurygenius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (see comment below), and is depicted on page 60. We herewith confirm the depicted specimen as a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer von Waldheim" authorityYear="1820" box="[1352,1436,685,710]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrochroidae" genus="Pedilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1352,1436,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Pedilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in a group of Сentral Asian species with red pronota), but it is impossible to recognize the species on basis of the photograph.
</paragraph>
